@joey0320 When a container runs out, it stays running for up to 50 milliseconds. In other words, it is hot for up to 50 milliseconds. This time is determined by pause-grace.
If no request is made to execute the function on the container within these 50 milliseconds, the container will be suspended for 10 minutes. In these 10 minutes, the container is warm and if requested, it will have a warm start. This time is determined by idle-container.
The pause container is a container which holds the network namespace for the pod.
